<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ881011-0126 </DOCNO><HL> Hadson, Virginia Electric Pact </HL><SO> </SO><CO> HAD </CO><DATELINE> OKLAHOMA CITY  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Hadson Corp. said its Ultrasystems Development Corp. unit signed contracts with Virginia Electric Power Co. calling for Ultrasystems to build four cogeneration units in Virginia.    Hadson said it expects the four units to cost more than $300 million, with construction to begin next year. Each plant is expected to generate about $30 million of electricity a year, which Hadson will sell under 25-year contracts to Virginia Electric, a unit of Dominion Energy Corp. The plants also will produce steam.    Hadson is an energy and defense concern. </TEXT></DOC>